import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', kde=True, label='Home Scores')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='away_score', kde=True, color='orange', label='Away Scores')
    
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores and away scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['score_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    avg_score_difference = data.groupby('date')['score_difference'].mean().reset_index()
    avg_score_difference['date'] = pd.to_datetime(avg_score_difference['date'], errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='date', y='score_difference', data=avg_score_difference)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average score difference between home and away teams?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_score_diff = data.groupby('division')['score_difference'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='division', y='score_difference', data=avg_score_diff)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which division has the highest average score difference?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data_melted = data.melt(id_vars=['home_team', 'away_team'], value_vars=['home_score', 'away_score'], var_name='score_type', value_name='score')
    sns.boxplot(x='score_type', y='score', data=data_melted)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of scores for each team?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
